source: a primitive root;
meaning: to "be high" actively, to "rise" or "raise" (in various applications, literally or figuratively)
usage: bring up, exalt (self), extol, give, go up, haughty, heave (up), (be, lift up on, make on, set up on, too) high(-er, one), hold up, levy, lift(-er) up, (be) lofty, (Ã— a-) loud, mount up, offer (up),   presumptuously, (be) promote(-ion), proud, set up, tall(-er), take (away, off, up), breed worms.
